{{update|date=November 2016}} {{Infobox Convention | image = | name = Arab Health | status = Active | genre = [[Healthcare]] | venue = [[Dubai International Convention Centre]] | location = [[Dubai]] | country = [[United Arab Emirates]] | first = 1975 | last = January 2018 | next = January 2019 | organizer = [[Informa]] Exhibitions | attendance = 84,500 (2018) | website = {{URL|www.arabhealthonline.com }} }}
'''Arab Health''' is a [[healthcare]] [[Academic conference|conference]] and [[trade show]] in the [[Middle East]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cooper|first1=Rachel|title=Life science firms Middle East-bound|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/pharmaceuticalsandchemicals/9015287/Life-science-firms-Middle-East-bound.html|accessdate=22 November 2014|work=The Telegraph|date=15 January 2012}}</ref> It first took place in [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]] in 1975. Healthcare industry representatives attend from the Middle East, Asia, Europe and the US.
== Exhibition and congress == The congress is one of the world's largest medical conferences.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sahoo|first1=Sananda|title=Arab Health shapes up robustly|url=http://www.thenational.ae/business/industry-insights/energy/arab-health-shapes-up-robustly#full|accessdate=22 November 2014|work=The National|publisher=Abu Dhabi Media|date=25 January 2014}}</ref>
Arab Health is supported by the UAE Ministry of Health, the Abu Dhabi Health Authority, the Dubai Health Authority and the Dubai Healthcare City Authority.
=== Awards === Awards are given for innovation and achievement in the industry. They include awards for [[radiology]], [[surgery]], [[medical laboratory|laboratory]] work, patient-centred care, and clinicians.
