'''Calcium fructoborate''' is an [[organic compound]] containing [[boron]] (and [[fructose]] and [[calcium]]). Its structural formula is Ca[(C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>10</sub>O<sub>6</sub>)<sub>2</sub>B]<sub>2</sub>∙4H<sub>2</sub>O.<ref>Chemnet. [http://www.chemnet.com/cas/de/250141-42-5/Calcium-fructoborate.html Calcium fructoborate at Chemnet] Page accessed April 9, 2016</ref>

It is naturally found in some plants, and is also manufactured and promoted as a [[dietary supplement]].<ref>[http://www.livestrong.com/article/501243-what-is-calcium-fructoborate/ What Is Calcium Fructoborate?]</ref>

