{{About|the crater on Mars|the crater on the Moon|Huxley (lunar crater)}} {{Infobox Mars crater | name = Huxley Crater | image = HuxleyMartianCrater.jpg | caption = Location of Huxley Crater | region = [[Hellas quadrangle]] | coordinates = {{coord|63|S|100.8|E|globe:mars_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | discoverer = | diameter = 107 km | eponym = [[Thomas Henry Huxley]] }} [[File:Wikihuxley.jpg|thumb|Huxley Crater, as seen by CTX camera (on Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter).]]
'''Huxley''' is a crater in the [[Hellas quadrangle]] of [[Mars]], located at 63.0°S latitude and 259.2°W longitude. It is 107.0&nbsp;km in diameter and was named after [[Thomas Henry Huxley]], and the name was approved in 1973 by the International Astronomical Union (IAU) Working Group for Planetary System Nomenclature (WGPSN).<ref>{{cite web|title=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature {{!}} Huxley|url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/2595|website=usgs.gov|publisher=[[International Astronomical Union]]|accessdate=4 March 2015}}</ref>
Huxley is due south of the larger [[Secchi (Martian crater)|Secchi]], other nearby named craters include [[Redi (crater)|Redi]] to the northwest, Laylá to the northeast and the [[Heinlein (Martian crater)|Heinlein]]-[[Weinbaum (Martian crater)|Weinbaum]] crater pair to the east-southeast, no nearby named craters are located south but another crater named [[Gilbert (Martian crater)|Gilbert]] is in the southwest.
==See also== * [[Climate of Mars]] * [[Geology of Mars]] * [[Impact crater]] * [[Impact event]] * [[List of craters on Mars]] * [[Ore resources on Mars]] * [[Planetary nomenclature]]
