{{no footnotes|date=March 2013}} {{Infobox organization |name = International Union of Nutritional Sciences |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = IUNS |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = IUNS |motto = |formation = {{start date and age|1948}} |extinction = |type = [[International nongovernmental organization|INGO]] |status = |purpose = |headquarters = |location = Vienna, Austria |region_served = Worldwide |membership = |language = English |leader_title = President |leader_name = Anna Lartey, Ghana |main_organ = |parent_organization = [[International Council for Science]] |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.iuns.org/ IUNS Official website] |remarks = }}
The '''International Union of Nutritional Sciences''' ('''IUNS''') is an international [[non-governmental organization]] established in 1948 to devote the advancement of [[nutrition]]. Since its 1948 foundation, the membership has grown to include 82 national adhering bodies and 16 affiliations.
==IUNS International Congresses== {| !Year !City !Country !Number of Delegates !Countries attending |- | 1948 | [[London]] | {{GBR}} | 22 | 13 |- | 1952 | [[Basel]] | {{SUI}} | 150 | 18 |- | 1954 | [[Amsterdam]] | {{NED}} | 360 | 32 |- | 1957 | [[Paris]] | {{FRA}} | 1000 | 22 |- | 1960 | [[Washington, D.C.]] | {{USA}} | 2000 | 65 |- | 1963 | [[Edinburgh]] | {{GBR}} | 1500 | 63 |- | 1966 | [[Hamburg]] | {{FRG}} | 2100 | 81 |- | 1969 | [[Prague]] | {{TCH}} | 1800 | 62 |- | 1972 | [[Mexico City]] | {{MEX}} | 2000 | 66 |- | 1975 | [[Kyoto]] | {{JPN}} | 2300 | 55 |- | 1978 | [[Rio de Janeiro]] | {{BRA}} | 3500 | 92 |- | 1981 | [[San Diego]] | {{USA}} | 2500 | 83 |- | 1985 | [[Brighton]] | {{GBR}} | 2300 | 92 |- | 1989 | [[Seoul]] | {{KOR}} | 3500 | 104 |- | 1993 | [[Adelaide]] | {{AUS}} | 2600 | 91 |- | 1997 | [[Montreal]] | {{CAN}} | 3250 | 92 |- | 2001 | [[Vienna]] | {{AUT}} | 3550 | 113 |- | 2005 | [[Durban]] | {{RSA}} | 2100 | 92 |- | 2009 | [[Bangkok]] | {{THA}} | 4070 | 106 |- | 2013 | [[Granada]] | {{ESP}} | 3896 | |- | 2017 | [[Argentina]] - scheduled for 2017 | {{ARG}} | | |}
==Governing Council== The Council consists of 5 Officers, the President, President-Elect, Vice-President, Secretary-General, Treasurer, Immediate Past-President, and six Council members. IUNS's current council consists of the following: - President: Anna Lartey [[Ghana]]; - Vice President: V. Prakash India; - President Elect: Alfredo Martinez Hernandez Spain; - Secretary General: Catherine Geissler UK; - Treasurer: Helmut Heseker Germany; - Member: Lynette Neufeld Canada; - Member: S. K. Roy [[Bangladesh]]; - Member: Godwin D. Ndossi [[Tanzania]]; - Member: Andrew Prentice UK; - Member: Teruo Miyazawa Japan; - Member: Reynaldo Martorell United States - Immediate Past-President: Ibrahim Elmadfa Austria; - Immediate Past Secretary General: Rekia Belahsen [[Morocco]];
==Headquarters== IUNS is registered in [[Vienna, Austria]].
==Secretariat== IUNS; The Nutrition Society; 10 Cambridge Court; 210 Shepherds Bush Road; London; UK; W6 7NJ
